
------------------------------------------------------------EXPERIMENT4---------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------Update the price of a particular product.--------------------------------------------------------------







mysql> select * from prdt;
+------+-----------+-------+
| p_id | p_name    | price |
+------+-----------+-------+
|  131 | iphone    | 12000 |
|  132 | backcover |   100 |
|  133 | chip      |    70 |
|  134 | harddisk  |  7000 |
|  135 | speaker   |  8000 |
+------+-----------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


mysql> update prdt set price=15000 where p_id=131;
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.05 sec)
Rows matched: 1  Changed: 1  Warnings: 0



mysql> select * from prdt;
+------+-----------+-------+
| p_id | p_name    | price |
+------+-----------+-------+
|  131 | iphone    | 15000 |
|  132 | backcover |   100 |
|  133 | chip      |   70 |
|  134 | harddisk  |  7000 |
|  135 | speaker   |  8000 |
+------+-----------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)





--------------------Change the name of city ‘calicut’ to ‘kozhikode’in the customertable--------------------------------------------


